  "content": "Best AI show I've been to in the past year. hashtag#ReutersMomentum surfaced the real challenges that enterprise leaders are facing in AI adoption.I spoke to 35+ Directors, VPs, and C-Suite AI Leaders from the world's biggest players in banking, financial services, insurance, healthcare, logistics, retail, and more... here's what I learned:Everyone wants to scale AI, and they're all facing similar challenges.Let's start with uses cases. What are the areas of opportunity?üè† Internal productivity use cases came first - faster, safer, clearer ROIüôÖ Customer-facing AI lags due to brand risk and complianceüíµ Revenue-driving use cases are now becoming a focus - leaders want impact on customers and the top lineSo how are leaders managing these initiatives from the top-down?üëÆ AI Centers of Excellence and Responsible AI boards are stepping up - aligning priorities, enforcing standards, and protecting the enterprise as AI adoption growsüß± But with that rigor comes real friction - POCs often stall under reviews, audits, infra checks, and layered approvalsMeanwhile...‚ö° Business units often end up working in silos, chasing best-of-breed tools for their own needs‚ö†Ô∏è This can be fast and effective locally, but without a unified strategy, this may lead to tech debt and fragmentationAnd then there's the big question: Buy or Build?üèóÔ∏è Hyperscalers, legacy platforms, and in-house teams are already a part of the enterprise ecosystem, and building on those seems logical - but depending on the use case, they can be slow, expensive, and full of false startsü§ñ Best-of-breed, GenAI-native vendors? Faster to deploy, easier to iterate, and built around highly specialized use cases - but also newer and subject to greater scrutinySo what‚Äôs the path forward?ü´° The smartest leaders are finding ways to move fast and build responsibly, while selecting the right partners to help scale adoption and maintain agility. But there's no one-size-fits-all approach. Only time will tell!Parloa Reuters Events Kelly Kirkwood Rob Murphy Meghan Kenny Paul Windom hashtag#MomentumAI hashtag#ReutersEvents hashtag#EnterpriseAI hashtag#AIAdoption hashtag#ResponsibleAI hashtag#DigitalTransformation hashtag#VoiceAI hashtag#CustomerExperience hashtag#AILeadership hashtag#Parloa",
